526
00:41:39,864 --> 00:41:43,233
Besides getting drunk
and crashing cars?

527
00:41:46,604 --> 00:41:48,805
Oh! Sorry I'm late!

528
00:41:48,807 --> 00:41:50,974
Oh! I completely forgot.

529
00:41:52,209 --> 00:41:53,710
Menopause.

530
00:41:54,820 --> 00:41:57,180
- Would you like something to drink?
- Oh, yes.

531
00:41:57,182 --> 00:41:59,983
Vodka and orange.

532
00:41:59,985 --> 00:42:05,088
Mmm, better not. I always
end up in the wrong bed.

533
00:42:05,923 --> 00:42:08,324
So, how's the newcomer?

534
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:13,496
Have they told you
not to date boys...

535
00:42:13,498 --> 00:42:16,299
- Jess!
- Or make any other big decisions yet?

536
00:42:16,301 --> 00:42:19,936
- Just ignore her, Gracie.
- Okay, okay.

537
00:42:19,938 --> 00:42:23,273
I think this girl needs
to have some real fun.

538
00:42:26,110 --> 00:42:29,145
What do ya say, Gracie?

539
00:42:53,504 --> 00:42:57,840
I met the love of my life
when I was 21 years old.

540
00:42:57,842 --> 00:43:01,044
Met him in a bar, of course.

541
00:43:01,046 --> 00:43:04,747
Oh, he was a great surfer.

542
00:43:04,749 --> 00:43:08,818
I didn't really even
like him much...

543
00:43:08,820 --> 00:43:11,421
in the beginning.

544
00:43:11,423 --> 00:43:13,756
But as time went by,

545
00:43:13,758 --> 00:43:16,960
he slowly took over my life.

546
00:43:17,761 --> 00:43:19,596
First time he hit me,

547
00:43:19,598 --> 00:43:23,099
we were at a drive-through
on our way to a party.

548
00:43:23,101 --> 00:43:25,168
I ordered the wrong drink,

549
00:43:25,170 --> 00:43:27,670
and he banged my head
off the car window.

550
00:43:27,672 --> 00:43:29,272
Oh, my God.

551
00:43:29,274 --> 00:43:32,308
I threatened to leave him
if he ever touched me again,

552
00:43:32,310 --> 00:43:36,179
as I did every time
it happened after that.

553
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:38,815
But I went back.

554
00:43:38,817 --> 00:43:42,285
I went back again
and again and again.

555
00:43:42,287 --> 00:43:45,355
- Why?
- Because I'm an addict.

556
00:43:46,957 --> 00:43:49,459
I always go back.

557
00:43:50,661 --> 00:43:54,831
When I finally got sober,
he just found another victim.

558
00:43:54,833 --> 00:43:56,532
That sucks.

559
00:43:56,534 --> 00:43:58,835
I'm sorry. That's
a really shitty story.

560
00:43:58,837 --> 00:44:02,038
That's okay.
I got married to Tom.

561
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:04,273
He's a nice guy.

562
00:44:06,076 --> 00:44:08,878
It hurts being like us, Gracie.

563
00:44:08,880 --> 00:44:12,148
I never felt comfortable
in my own skin.

564
00:44:12,150 --> 00:44:15,618
So I drank to be sexy.

565
00:44:16,787 --> 00:44:19,355
I did cocaine to be thin.

566
00:44:19,357 --> 00:44:22,225
I tortured myself
with plastic surgery...

567
00:44:22,227 --> 00:44:26,429
to... to look young
and be beautiful.

568
00:44:27,998 --> 00:44:30,233
And for what?

569
00:44:30,235 --> 00:44:33,002
I manufactured a woman...

570
00:44:33,004 --> 00:44:35,071
that I don't even like.

571
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:41,110
You know, I... I don't know the
first thing about being sober.

572
00:44:43,447 --> 00:44:45,715
But I hope
you find your way out.

573
00:44:52,756 --> 00:44:54,323
Gotta go.

574
00:44:55,759 --> 00:44:58,594
- Do you want a ride?
- No, it's okay. I'll walk.

575
00:45:03,067 --> 00:45:05,168
Good-bye, Gracie.

576
00:45:06,270 --> 00:45:07,704
Bye.

577
00:46:09,366 --> 00:46:11,334
Hey!

578
00:46:11,336 --> 00:46:13,336
- I thought you weren't gonna show.
- Yeah.

579
00:46:13,338 --> 00:46:15,805
- Hi, Gracie!
- Hi.

580
00:46:15,807 --> 00:46:18,374
What's up, girl?

581
00:46:19,263 --> 00:46:21,544
Yo. What time's
the movie?

582
00:46:21,546 --> 00:46:23,279
7:30.
7:30?

583
00:46:23,281 --> 00:46:25,782
You can just hang out here.

584
00:46:25,784 --> 00:46:28,017
7:30?
I... I... I can't go.

585
00:46:28,019 --> 00:46:29,552
Why not?

586
00:46:29,554 --> 00:46:32,255
Um, I have to go to a meeting.

587
00:46:32,257 --> 00:46:34,791
You... have to go?

588
00:46:34,793 --> 00:46:37,393
Yeah, yeah. She got a court order.
She hit a cop.

589
00:46:37,395 --> 00:46:39,028
- Yeah.
- I did not hit a cop.

590
00:46:39,030 --> 00:46:41,531
- Aw!
- It was an accident.

591
00:46:41,533 --> 00:46:44,200
Oh, yes.
An accident, for sure.

592
00:46:44,202 --> 00:46:46,536
Oh, my God. Is there anything
secret in this town?

593
00:46:46,538 --> 00:46:49,405
Uh... no.
No.

594
00:46:49,407 --> 00:46:51,374
- Definitely not.
- All right.

595
00:46:51,376 --> 00:46:55,044
- Well...
- Hey, I'll come with you.

596
00:46:55,046 --> 00:46:56,946
Can always use
another meeting, you know.

597
00:46:56,948 --> 00:46:59,448
Well, I thought we were... Can't
we go to, like, the 9:00?

598
00:46:59,450 --> 00:47:02,685
Dude. Catch up with you later.
Yeah?

599
00:47:02,687 --> 00:47:05,354
Totally.
Yeah?

600
00:47:05,356 --> 00:47:07,256
Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Cool.

601
00:47:07,258 --> 00:47:09,125
- Bye.
- Bye.

602
00:47:09,127 --> 00:47:10,660
I gotta go.
See ya.

603
00:47:15,466 --> 00:47:18,134
Okay, everybody.
Let's start our meeting, huh?

604
00:47:18,776 --> 00:47:21,537
- Guys wanna start a meeting?
- Yeah.

605
00:47:21,539 --> 00:47:23,539
Yeah? Yeah? Good.

606
00:47:23,541 --> 00:47:25,141
All right.
Hello, everyone.

607
00:47:25,143 --> 00:47:29,278
Welcome to "We Are Not a Glum Lot"
meeting of Alcoholics Anonymous.

608
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:32,248
My name is David,
and I am an alcoholic.

609
00:47:32,250 --> 00:47:34,851
Hi, David.

610
00:47:34,853 --> 00:47:37,486
Uh, can somebody read the blue card?
Who'd I give that to?

611
00:47:37,488 --> 00:47:39,622
- Oh. That was me.
- Ah. Marijane. Excellent.

612
00:47:39,624 --> 00:47:41,891
Hi, I'm Marijane,
and I'm an alcoholic.

613
00:47:41,893 --> 00:47:43,559
Hi, Marijane.

614
00:47:43,561 --> 00:47:45,962
"This is an open meeting
of Alcoholics Anonymous.

615
00:47:45,964 --> 00:47:49,165
We are glad you are all here,
especially newcomers.

616
00:47:49,167 --> 00:47:53,035
In keeping with our singleness of
purpose and our third tradition,

617
00:47:53,037 --> 00:47:55,938
which states that the only
requirement for AA membership...

618
00:47:55,940 --> 00:47:58,074
is a desire to stop drinking,

619
00:47:58,076 --> 00:47:59,575
we ask that all
who participate..."

620
00:47:59,577 --> 00:48:01,510
It reminded me
of when we were married.

621
00:48:01,512 --> 00:48:03,976
He always reacted to
everything by screaming

622
00:48:04,002 --> 00:48:05,948
and yelling, and
it was just awful.

623
00:48:05,950 --> 00:48:08,217
And I reacted by drinking.

624
00:48:08,219 --> 00:48:10,820
- You holding out on me?
- A bottle of wine, rum, whatever it was.

625
00:48:10,822 --> 00:48:14,123
Thank you, guys, for all
your help and your support.

626
00:48:14,125 --> 00:48:18,361
You've been a wonder for me. Thank
you so much for everything.

627
00:48:18,363 --> 00:48:21,497
Okay, uh, who's next?

628
00:48:27,604 --> 00:48:30,339
I'm Rosemarie,
and I'm an alcoholic.

629
00:48:30,341 --> 00:48:32,408
Hi, Rosemarie.

630
00:48:32,410 --> 00:48:35,645
Um, I didn't have
a drink today,

631
00:48:35,647 --> 00:48:40,316
so I'm
a rip-roaring success.

632
00:48:40,318 --> 00:48:47,823
But, uh, I can't stay sober
unless I get sober.

633
00:48:47,825 --> 00:48:51,661
Ninety-nine percent of my problems
go away when I don't drink.

634
00:48:51,663 --> 00:48:55,531
But abstinence is not sobriety.

635
00:49:00,203 --> 00:49:03,372
No one ever forced
a drink down my throat.

636
00:49:05,042 --> 00:49:07,376
I drank because, um,

637
00:49:08,278 --> 00:49:10,758
I liked the effect
produced by alcohol.

638
00:49:12,115 --> 00:49:14,984
Alcohol suppressed my growth.

639
00:49:14,986 --> 00:49:16,585
It, um,

640
00:49:17,788 --> 00:49:21,023
prevented me from having
adult relationships...

641
00:49:21,025 --> 00:49:25,394
because it was easier
to get drunk than to grow.

642
00:49:25,396 --> 00:49:27,563
I escaped my problems,
but at the same time...

643
00:49:27,565 --> 00:49:30,866
I ignored my responsibilities.

644
00:49:32,169 --> 00:49:35,571
I had to learn to grow up.

645
00:49:45,015 --> 00:49:46,916
That's all.

646
00:49:48,452 --> 00:49:50,019
Okay, who's next?

647
00:49:51,388 --> 00:49:53,656
- Um...
- Gracie.

648
00:49:53,658 --> 00:49:55,925
Yeah. Told you that
last night.

649
00:49:55,927 --> 00:49:57,460
Sorry.
Remember?

650
00:49:58,729 --> 00:50:01,330
Yeah, I'm Gracie, and I'm, um,

651
00:50:04,434 --> 00:50:06,869
here, I guess...

652
00:50:07,971 --> 00:50:10,573
Um...

653
00:50:10,575 --> 00:50:12,975
I mean, I was
court-ordered to be here,

654
00:50:12,977 --> 00:50:16,979
so I guess I wouldn't choose
to be here if I had a choice.

655
00:50:16,981 --> 00:50:18,914
But I don't. Um...

656
00:50:21,266 --> 00:50:23,586
No, you know why
I'm actually here?

657
00:50:23,588 --> 00:50:26,856
I'm actually here because my
dad turned his back on me.

658
00:50:26,858 --> 00:50:29,792
He also abandoned my mom 15 years
ago and let her die alone,

659
00:50:29,794 --> 00:50:32,278
so I guess I shouldn't
really be holding out

660
00:50:32,304 --> 00:50:34,597
for any kind of big
daddy reconciliation.

661
00:50:34,599 --> 00:50:36,880
I mean, people
are selfish, right?

662
00:50:38,368 --> 00:50:40,603
You really wanna tell me
to "grow up"?

663
00:50:40,605 --> 00:50:43,773
What, you don't like the way I am?
I don't care!

664
00:50:43,775 --> 00:50:46,642
This is a free country.
Right?

665
00:50:46,644 --> 00:50:49,779
Why won't anybody just leave me
alone to do what I want to do?

666
00:50:49,781 --> 00:50:52,003
I mean, this is my life!
If I want to get

667
00:50:52,029 --> 00:50:54,408
wasted, why is that
anybody else's business?

668
00:50:58,422 --> 00:51:01,490
Oh, no.
My name is Jessie.

669
00:51:04,327 --> 00:51:07,496
And... I need
to tell you the truth.

670
00:51:12,569 --> 00:51:14,737
And you're not gonna
stop me, Marijane.

671
00:51:14,739 --> 00:51:18,707
- Jessie, why don't you come in and sit
down with us? - I don't wanna sit down!

672
00:51:18,709 --> 00:51:22,311
And I don't wanna
talk to you, Rosemarie!

673
00:51:22,313 --> 00:51:25,081
And I don't wanna talk
to you, Saint Sonia!

674
00:51:28,051 --> 00:51:29,585
I don't want you...

675
00:51:29,587 --> 00:51:32,455
to tell me to accept it.

676
00:51:33,250 --> 00:51:35,491
I don't want to be sober.

677
00:51:35,493 --> 00:51:38,661
It hurts too much.
The pain is too great.

678
00:51:38,663 --> 00:51:41,297
- We love you, Jessie.
- I don't want you to love me.

679
00:51:41,299 --> 00:51:44,166
But we do.
We love you, baby.

680
00:51:44,168 --> 00:51:46,569
You're all a bunch of phonies.

681
00:51:46,571 --> 00:51:50,139
You are. You're all a bunch of...
a bunch of liars.

682
00:51:50,141 --> 00:51:52,108
None of you are sober.

683
00:51:53,243 --> 00:51:55,578
I hate this place.
I hate these rooms!

684
00:51:55,580 --> 00:51:58,948
Jessie? Jessie, come on.

685
00:52:06,089 --> 00:52:09,492
No, Jessie! Jessie, no!
I've gotta pee!

686
00:52:09,494 --> 00:52:11,527
I've got to pee!
I know.

687
00:52:11,529 --> 00:52:14,830
We're not gonna do that here. We're
gonna go home. I'm gonna get you home.

688
00:52:14,832 --> 00:52:17,967
Marijane, you're no fun.
I know, I know.

689
00:52:17,969 --> 00:52:21,370
I'm a big ol' fuddy-duddy,
but that's the way it is.

690
00:52:21,372 --> 00:52:22,805
Here we go.
Get her in.

691
00:52:22,807 --> 00:52:25,474
Let's go party!

692
00:52:25,476 --> 00:52:27,543
Let's go party!

693
00:52:27,545 --> 00:52:29,478
We're gonna go party
at your house, baby.

694
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:31,947
Got a seat?
Hi.

695
00:52:31,949 --> 00:52:34,850
Oh, Marijane! Oh, my God.
What happened?

696
00:52:34,852 --> 00:52:38,154
Rosemarie's gonna drive you.
She got wasted.

697
00:52:39,523 --> 00:52:42,158
But that's nobody else's
business, is it?

698
00:52:48,798 --> 00:52:52,368
Party! Party!
Let's go party!

699
00:52:52,370 --> 00:52:54,651
You wanna get out of here?

700
00:52:58,008 --> 00:52:59,742
Come on.

701
00:53:03,813 --> 00:53:05,481
God.

702
00:53:06,149 --> 00:53:07,883
Crazy.

703
00:53:19,696 --> 00:53:21,964
So you're all
just lying, right?

704
00:53:22,933 --> 00:53:24,733
What?

705
00:53:24,735 --> 00:53:28,070
Does anybody
actually like being sober?

706
00:53:29,105 --> 00:53:32,274
I mean, I'm on day two,
and it sucks already.

707
00:53:34,110 --> 00:53:37,146
- I mean, it gets better.
- Jessie didn't think so.

708
00:53:37,148 --> 00:53:41,517
Well, some people
just... never get it.

709
00:53:41,519 --> 00:53:43,752
I don't get it.

710
00:53:44,221 --> 00:53:45,888
I don't.

711
00:53:45,890 --> 00:53:48,090
I mean,
why did you stop partying?

712
00:53:48,092 --> 00:53:50,092
- Well, I mean, I...
- Don't bullshit me.

713
00:53:50,094 --> 00:53:52,728
I want the truth.
Why'd you stop partying?

714
00:53:55,799 --> 00:53:57,800
Well...

715
00:53:59,603 --> 00:54:03,505
I lost a music scholarship
after my second DUI.

716
00:54:03,507 --> 00:54:07,676
First they just kinda
counted it as a bad day.

717
00:54:08,645 --> 00:54:12,581
Second one meant
that I had a bad habit.

718
00:54:13,850 --> 00:54:18,821
So now, instead of cuttin'
waves between class in Malibu,

719
00:54:19,789 --> 00:54:22,791
I'm cuttin' grass
between waves...

720
00:54:22,793 --> 00:54:24,260
here.

721
00:54:43,179 --> 00:54:46,849
You know, I hung out with her today
and she was actually really cool.

722
00:54:46,851 --> 00:54:49,618
She's a chronic relapser.

723
00:54:49,620 --> 00:54:51,186
She'll be back.

724
00:54:52,522 --> 00:54:54,690
If she ever
gets over the shame.

725
00:54:54,692 --> 00:54:56,292
Oh.
Yeah.

726
00:54:56,294 --> 00:54:58,127
I can't even...

727
00:54:58,129 --> 00:54:59,728
That was a little...

728
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:06,035
What brought you
to New Smyrna Beach?

729
00:55:12,175 --> 00:55:14,043
Mommy?

730
00:55:14,045 --> 00:55:15,744
Oh, I see.

731
00:55:15,746 --> 00:55:17,313
She's got secrets.

732
00:55:17,315 --> 00:55:21,550
Get off of me!
I hate you so much!

733
00:55:21,552 --> 00:55:23,452
- I hate you!
- Do not do this!

734
00:55:23,454 --> 00:55:26,655
- Mommy
- Leave me alone!

735
00:55:28,558 --> 00:55:31,060
I came here once
when I was a kid.

736
00:55:33,463 --> 00:55:35,331
Before my mom died.

737
00:55:39,502 --> 00:55:41,203
How'd she die?

738
00:55:42,272 --> 00:55:43,972
How do you think?

739
00:55:51,214 --> 00:55:53,148
You know what?

740
00:55:53,150 --> 00:55:54,616
Wait right here.

741
00:55:54,618 --> 00:55:57,086
Where are you going?

742
00:55:58,121 --> 00:55:59,788
Don't move!

743
00:55:59,790 --> 00:56:02,858
I got a surprise for you
back in the truck!

744
00:56:21,044 --> 00:56:22,544
Seriously?

745
00:56:22,546 --> 00:56:25,386
Does it look like I'm joking?
No.

746
00:56:25,648 --> 00:56:28,584
Surf'll be good tomorrow.

747
00:56:28,586 --> 00:56:31,253
Always is after a full moon.

748
00:56:32,689 --> 00:56:34,323
Did you know...

749
00:56:35,792 --> 00:56:39,995
that all the tides of the
earth come from the moon?

