998
01:20:20,683 --> 01:20:23,050
No, I won't leave you alone!
I hate you!

999
01:20:27,223 --> 01:20:29,523
Get away from me!

1000
01:20:36,698 --> 01:20:38,399
I hate you.

1001
01:20:57,018 --> 01:20:59,353
Come on, Mommy.

1002
01:21:05,327 --> 01:21:08,495
Why did you leave me, Mom?

1003
01:21:12,601 --> 01:21:14,568
Why did you do it?

1004
01:21:22,210 --> 01:21:25,312
Wasn't I worth being well for?

1005
01:21:29,685 --> 01:21:33,320
Why didn't you take care of me?

1006
01:21:37,592 --> 01:21:41,228
Because she was ill, Gracie.

1007
01:21:42,464 --> 01:21:45,833
And if I could change the
past for you, I would do it.

1008
01:21:48,937 --> 01:21:50,571
I would.

1009
01:21:58,246 --> 01:22:00,781
But we can't change the past.

1010
01:22:04,167 --> 01:22:06,287
If I could, I would've
done it 11 years ago...

1011
01:22:06,289 --> 01:22:08,956
when my daughter died
of that overdose.

1012
01:22:12,127 --> 01:22:15,396
And every night since then
I go to sleep,

1013
01:22:15,398 --> 01:22:18,465
and I imagine
how I could've stopped it.

1014
01:22:24,739 --> 01:22:26,774
But I was too ill.

1015
01:22:31,546 --> 01:22:33,213
I hate her.

1016
01:22:33,215 --> 01:22:35,282
Oh, God, no.

1017
01:22:35,284 --> 01:22:37,445
Don't say that, Gracie.

1018
01:22:40,388 --> 01:22:42,623
How do I not hate her?

1019
01:22:46,695 --> 01:22:49,997
She missed everything
I needed her for.

1020
01:22:53,268 --> 01:22:55,736
She missed everything
that mattered.

1021
01:22:59,741 --> 01:23:01,742
I needed her.

1022
01:23:05,714 --> 01:23:07,715
I had no one...

1023
01:23:09,184 --> 01:23:11,719
to talk to when I got lost.

1024
01:23:14,289 --> 01:23:15,956
Yeah.

1025
01:23:17,993 --> 01:23:19,660
I do.

1026
01:23:23,098 --> 01:23:24,898
I hate her.

1027
01:23:44,152 --> 01:23:46,086
I don't trust anybody.

1028
01:23:50,925 --> 01:23:52,860
And it's because of her.

1029
01:23:57,599 --> 01:23:59,566
Grace.

1030
01:23:59,568 --> 01:24:01,668
Where are you gonna go?
Grace?

1031
01:24:14,015 --> 01:24:16,417
Sonia?

1032
01:24:18,086 --> 01:24:19,753
Sonia!

1033
01:24:22,090 --> 01:24:24,925
Gracie!
Where's Sonia?

1034
01:24:24,927 --> 01:24:26,427
Why?
What's going on?

1035
01:24:26,429 --> 01:24:29,129
Sonia!
It's Jessie!

1036
01:24:29,131 --> 01:24:30,798
Come on!

1037
01:24:33,601 --> 01:24:35,369
Let's go!

1038
01:24:42,077 --> 01:24:44,378
Wait!

1039
01:24:51,159 --> 01:24:53,320
She crashed her car
up by 1-95.

1040
01:24:53,322 --> 01:24:56,290
They took her into surgery a
couple of hours ago. Was it bad?

1041
01:24:56,292 --> 01:25:00,094
Where's Tom? He went to get a
cup of coffee a while ago.

1042
01:25:00,096 --> 01:25:02,162
Oh, here he is.
Tom? Hey.

1043
01:25:07,869 --> 01:25:11,371
She's been drunk
since yesterday.

1044
01:25:11,373 --> 01:25:15,642
They said she was doing 90 miles
an hour when she lost control.

1045
01:25:15,644 --> 01:25:18,545
I'm sure the doctors
are gonna do every...

1046
01:25:23,318 --> 01:25:26,453
- We did what we could.
- Oh, my God!

1047
01:25:26,455 --> 01:25:28,789
I'm so sorry.
Oh, my God.

1048
01:25:28,791 --> 01:25:32,192
Oh, my God.
I'm so sorry.

1049
01:25:40,068 --> 01:25:41,935
I'm so sorry.

1050
01:25:41,937 --> 01:25:44,538
I'm so sorry.

1051
01:25:51,346 --> 01:25:54,581
[ Dispatcher, Indistinct ]

1052
01:27:16,464 --> 01:27:18,065
Thank you.

1053
01:28:03,611 --> 01:28:05,612
It is my great pleasure...

1054
01:28:05,614 --> 01:28:08,982
to introduce
tonight's speaker, Gracie.

1055
01:28:17,293 --> 01:28:19,726
Whoo!

1056
01:28:22,430 --> 01:28:25,032
Hi. I'm Gracie.
I'm an alcoholic.

1057
01:28:25,034 --> 01:28:27,334
Hi, Gracie!
Hi.

1058
01:28:27,336 --> 01:28:31,972
I think I know all of you and have gotten
to know all of you over the years.

1059
01:28:31,974 --> 01:28:36,009
I don't know why all of you,
especially my family,

1060
01:28:36,011 --> 01:28:39,279
put up with the person I was
when I landed here.

1061
01:28:39,281 --> 01:28:43,250
All I know for sure is that a
community of strangers loved me...

1062
01:28:43,252 --> 01:28:45,852
until I could love myself.

1063
01:28:45,854 --> 01:28:48,588
This disease has claimed
so many lives,

1064
01:28:48,590 --> 01:28:51,091
including my mom and...

1065
01:28:51,093 --> 01:28:52,893
our Jessie.

1066
01:28:52,895 --> 01:28:55,696
I-I am just so grateful
to all of you...

1067
01:28:55,698 --> 01:28:59,032
for guiding me
into this new way of life.

